      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE PRIESTESS (3) came from a 40m handicap and broke early so did well to get within 3.4m of the winner here on Tuesday. Had been midfield in a Group 1 for the mares two back and put together a string of wins prior. Better off behind a mobile and should get her chance from this draw. Former Kiwi PARAMOUNT KIWI NZ (6) makes his first Australian appearance. Has joined Jason Grimson since placing in two preparatory trials last month. Hart drives so could kick off with a win. I AM HELLBOUND (9) led and dug deep to take out a standing start race over 2300m last week, getting home by just a nose. Interesting to see what unfolds from this wide draw but he has built a good record at this circuit and distance. YOUR MAJESTY (10) came from this barrier for a first-up win by 4 metres at this circuit and distance. Could go on with it.",
